# .gitattributes
# ---------------
# Normalises line endings to LF for all text files when checked out on any OS.
# This prevents ruff (and other Unix tools running in CI on Linux) from seeing
# CRLF line endings and flagging files as needing reformatting.
#
# How it works:
#   text=auto  — Git decides if a file is text and normalises on commit.
#   eol=lf     — Forces LF line endings on checkout for the matched patterns.
#
# Windows developers: Git will convert CRLF → LF on commit and LF → CRLF on
# checkout only if core.autocrlf is set. With eol=lf here, checkouts always
# produce LF, so editors and tools see consistent line endings.

# Default for all text files
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicitly mark binary files to prevent any conversion
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.tar binary
*.gz binary
*.wasm binary
